page.title: 05BECKWITHSHAW VILLAGE
page.content: In Beckwithshaw there are six semi detached houses built about a hundred years ago and new houses built three years ago. These new ones are in a small estate and there is a small council terrace. Most people have lived here for no more than ten years with a lot living here less than five years.This is because there are new houses built , but in the older houses one person has lived here for sixty years. Before living here people lived at Leeds and Harrogate and moved here because it is in the countryside and quiet. To improve the village people would like to see less heavy traffic, a footpath on both sides of the road and the speed limit recognised.Others would like a shop so that they don't have to go to Harrogate for things.
